data.enText: a line that goes around a circle or any other curved shape; the length of this line

data.chText: 地球的周长大约为25 000英里。
data.enText: The earth is almost 25 000 miles in circumference .

simple_means.memory_skill: circum 环绕，周围 + fer 带来 + ence 表状态 → 来环绕一圈 → 周长

tr: the size of something as given by the distance around it
the length of the closed curve of a circle
the boundary line encompassing an area or object
example: he had walked the full circumference of his land
a danger to all races over the whole circumference of the globe

value.def: The circumference of a circle, place, or round object is the distance around its edge.

example.tran: 计算地球周长的科学家

example.ex: The island is 3.5 km in circumference.

value.def: The circumference of a circle, place, or round object is its edge.

example.ex: Cut the salmon into long strips and wrap it round the circumference of the bread.
example.tran: 把鲑鱼切成长条，缠裹在面包上。

circum 环绕，周围 + navigate 航行 → 环航（世界）
